\series default

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang spanish
Alternativamente, se puede construir directamente una matriz que combine ambas operaciones:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang spanish

\begin_inset Formula \[p' = H \cdot p\]
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang spanish

\begin_inset Formula \[\begin{bmatrix} x' \\ y' \\ 1 \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} \cos(\theta) & -\sin(\theta) & t_x \\ \sin(\theta) & \cos(\theta) & t_y \\ 0 & 0 & 1 \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} x \\ y \\ 1 \end{bmatrix}\]
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang spanish
Expandiendo la multiplicación matricial:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang spanish

\begin_inset Formula \[x' = x\cos(\theta) - y\sin(\theta) + t_x\]
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[y' = x\sin(\theta) + y\cos(\theta) + t_y\]
\end_inset


\end_layout

